## Secrets management in .NET

```csharp
// Local development
dotnet user-secrets set "ConnectionStrings:Default" "Server=..."

// Production — Azure Key Vault with managed identity
builder.Configuration.AddAzureKeyVault(
    new Uri($"https://{vaultName}.vault.azure.net/"),
    new DefaultAzureCredential());
```

- Never add secrets to `appsettings.json` or `appsettings.{env}.json`
- Use `IOptions<T>` to access secrets from config; do not inject `IConfiguration` into domain or application layers
- Use managed identity in Azure; no credential strings in connection strings

