## Dependency vulnerability scanning

Add to CI pipeline:

```bash
dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive
```

Integrate with GitHub Dependabot or Azure DevOps security scanning for automated alerts.

---

## OWASP mitigations — .NET specific

| Risk | .NET implementation |
|------|-------------------|
| Injection | EF Core LINQ + FluentValidation |
| Auth failures | `AddJwtBearer` with strict token validation |
| Sensitive data | `[JsonIgnore]`, masked logs, Key Vault for secrets |
| XXE | `XmlReaderSettings { DtdProcessing = DtdProcessing.Prohibit }` |
| Broken access control | Policy-based auth + resource ownership in handlers |
| Security misconfiguration | Disable developer exception page in production; apply HSTS |
| XSS | `HtmlEncoder`; CSP headers |
| Insecure deserialisation | No `BinaryFormatter`; strict `System.Text.Json` |
| Vulnerable components | `dotnet list package --vulnerable`; Dependabot |
| Logging failures | Structured logs; alert on repeated auth failures |
